                        <h2 class="gcweb-heading-m">Before you start</h2>
                        <p>Get familair with design in Government.</p>
                        <p>The GOV.UK <a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual" target="_blank">Service Manual</a> and GOV.UK <a href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/">Design System</a> provides the core guidelines and standards we follow in DfE and across all central government departments and a lot of other public sector bodies and authorities.</p>
                        <p>Understand how the profession (service, interaction or content design) you'll be working in does things in DfE. We've published guidance for how we work and design user-centered, joined up, trusted services in this manual, for each profession.
                        </p>
                        <p>Read through the <a href="https://apply-the-service-standard.education.gov.uk/" target="_blank">How to apply the Service Standard in the Department for Education</a> manual and familiarise yourself with how we apply the 14 Service Standard in DfE throughout the delivery lifecycle.</p>
