                        <h2 class="gcweb-heading-m">How we do design in DfE</h2>
                        <p></p>
                        <h3 class="gcweb-heading-m">Protected time</h3>
                        <p>Every Thursday betwen 1pm and 5pm is community protected time. This allows you to work on community and professional develiopment instead of your usual project or delivery work.</p>
                        <p>Some examples of how this time has been used includes:</p>
                        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                        <li>creating an evolving set of design standards for all user-centered design professions</li>
                        <li>ways of working, <a href="/interaction-design/principle/">principles</a> and guidelines for good design practice</li>
                        <li>consistent approach to <a href="/design-assurance/design-critiques.html">design reviews and critiques</a></li>
                        <li>a process for creating and publishing <a href="/design-assurance/design-histories.html">design histories</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>                    
